Police arrested a 21-year-old man for possession of rhino horn in KaSiboshwa, Mpumalanga on Friday morning, Lowvelder reports. Police rushed to a house after receiving a tip-off. On arrival, while police were talking to the homeowner, they noticed a man in the backyard running with a black plastic bag. READ MORE: Mahlobo s rhino horn trafficking accuser goes into hiding &#8211; report They gave chase and apprehended the suspect as he was making his way towards a nearby sugar-cane farm. Police investigations are still continuing. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.